scheduled_maintenances.name: [GLOBAL][Dedicated Servers] - Debian 13/Proxmox 9 installation changes for UEFI boot servers

incident_updates.body: As part of our continuous improvement plan, a change is scheduled on the installation process for Debian 13 and Proxmox VE 9 installation on UEFI Dedicated servers. Start time : 12/11/2025 10:00 UTC End time : 12/11/2025 13:00 UTC Service impact : None Service improvement : Starting on 12/11/2025, all new Debian 13 and Proxmox 9 installations will feature an EFI System Partition (ESP) over RAID1 instead of several ESPs. Legacy boot servers are not affected. Please refer to https://community.ovhcloud.com/community/en/upcoming-change-efi-system-partition-over-raid1-for-linux-installations?id=community_question&sys_id=8602b59034ac7290f078f43c21c5a60d for additional information. Thank you for your understanding.
